!TextLint is a tool to check your scientific writing for common style errors.

Video of its integration within Emacs: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CsG2DKgHanE

Please follow the [https://github.com/DamienCassou/textlint#emacs-installing installation instructions] if you are interested.

It's written in Smalltalk and is currently accessible through:

* Emacs (https://github.com/DamienCassou/textlint) 
* [http://macromates.com/ TextMate]  (https://github.com/DamienCassou/textlint) Note: This is currently deprecated.
* The web (http://textlint.lukas-renggli.ch/)
* A Smalltalk IDE (http://scg.unibe.ch/research/textlint)

Don't hesitate to [https://github.com/DamienCassou/textlint#support ask for support].

